\b Brief Outline
\b0 \
In the first section, I shall \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
briefly review the virtue theory of Aristotle and the historical ascendancy of the Aristotelian virtue tradition in the English-speaking philosophy (via Elizabeth Anscombe, Peter Geach, and others). I situate virtue ethics within modern moral philosophy alongside deontology, consequentialism, and divine command theory. I also situate neo-Aristotelian naturalism within metaethical context of other moral naturalisms. \
